cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.PF, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the issue of interference in shared main memory systems, which is a common problem in operating systems (cs.OS) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also proposes techniques for providing quality-of-service guarantees and minimizing unfairness, which are topics in performance evaluation (cs.PF) and systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's focus on accurately estimating slowdowns could also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DC).
